# UI defaults (skeleton + i18n)

When writing or editing UI code, apply these by default.

## 1. Loading state — use PrimeNG Skeleton

- Use **&lt;p-skeleton&gt;** for loading; do not add spinners or new loading flags.
- Use existing loading flags only (e.g. `loading`, `loadingDetails`, `isLoading$`).
- Pattern: `*ngIf="loading; else realContent"` with `<ng-template #realContent>`; skeleton replaces inner content only; keep layout (containers, spacing, alignment) unchanged.
- Skeleton size must match the final content (height/width) to avoid layout shift.
- Do not change TypeScript logic; only change the HTML template.

## 2. Translations — everything in en + ar

- **Templates:** All user-visible text via `{{ 'key' | translate }}` or `[placeholder]="'key' | translate"`. Add keys to both `src/assets/i18n/en.json` and `src/assets/i18n/ar.json`.
- **Toaster / notifications (MessageService):** Never use hardcoded `summary` or `detail`. Use `this.translate.instant('key')` (or `translate.instant('key')`) and add those keys to both en.json and ar.json. Arabic: professional, formal UI Arabic.

Example toaster:

```ts
this.messageService.add({
  severity: 'success',
  summary: this.translate.instant('common.success'),
  detail: this.translate.instant('entityAccounts.messages.created')
});
```

Apply skeleton and i18n (including toasts) on every new or modified UI.
